@DATABASE "Dan Dare 2"
@NODE "MAIN" "SPECCY POKES - D - Dan Dare 2"
@TOC "MAIN"

                   ZX SPECTRUM (SPECCY heheh) POKES - D
                   ====================================

                                Dan Dare 2
                                ==========


DESCRIPTION              POKE
===========              ====

@{"Infinite Energy" RXS "ADDRESS COMMAND ZXAMPoke(58278,62) ZXAMPoke(58279,80) ZXAMPoke(58280,18) ZXAMPoke(58281,201)"}         58278,62:58279,80:58280,18:58281,201
@{"Infinite Time  " RXS "ADDRESS COMMAND ZXAMPoke(60677,0)"}         60677,0
@{"No Treens      " RXS "ADDRESS COMMAND ZXAMPoke(61827,0) ZXAMPoke(61840,0)"}         61827,0:61840.0
@{"Immunuty       " RXS "ADDRESS COMMAND ZXAMPoke(56382,201)"}         56382,201
@{"Infinite Lives " RXS "ADDRESS COMMAND ZXAMPoke(54390,0)"}         54390,0
@{"Lives = x      " RXS "ADDRESS COMMAND ZXAMPoke(53822,255) zxampoke(64594,255)"}         53822,x:64594,x (x= 1-255)


                         Change x to whatever value you wish, using
                         the POKE option on the ZXAM GUI. Simply
                         click the button to get the maximum value
                         x can be (usually 255).


                         The "No Treens" hack does work to a certain extent.
                         It seems to try to shoot as many of them as possible
                         whenever you enter a screen (I think?)

                         The "Lives = x" and "Infinite Lives" POKEs were by
                         me. Enjoy!

                         Rastan
@endnode
